<br>
1.5 Spec points per level seems kinda harsh. Possible templates:Although with the way the buffs work you may want High HtH, med savagery and med parry:<br>
<br>
Specs- 49 savagery, 39 HtH, 20 parry <br>
49 savagery, 44 HtH, 4 parry <br>
44 Savagery, 44 HtH, 21parry <br>
50 HtH, 43 Savagery, 2 parry <br>
<br>
Not many decent specs to balance high HtH and High savagery. I will probably do 49/44/4. <br>
<br>
HtH styles look to be harsh without a high level no opener style such as Ameythyst Slash or DF or others in the 29-34 range. Most are long chains which suck in RvR. <br>
<br>
HP on hybrid table with studded armor seems like it will make them damage dealers unable to take much of a beating. <br>
<br>
If the buffs are 30 sec they probably suck. 10 minute buffs on a Friar are harsh for having to recast all the time. 30 sec that take health to cast? Hmm <br>
<br>
Valkyn race seems gimp for any class really. Norse will make the best Savage with dex rising every level. Buffed at 50 with aug dex 1 or 2 you will have close or over 300 dex. <br>
<br>
I dunno, I was looking forward to the savage class. I was hoping for something like a Zerk with a couple cool things, but it looks like they are a mini zerk with some majar drawbacks in most aspects. <br>
<br>
Will have to try it and see, but it is doubtful they will be a decent RvR class. <br>
<br>
Also, Zerks get 2.0 spec per level with needing to spec 3 lines. Left Ax, Weapon and parry is all Zerks need to spec.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maihgreadtomanes>Maihgread Tomanes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(11/19/02 5:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.diary-x.com/users/avedon/maih2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on Savages</span><hr size=1> I agree completely.<br>
